.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH oxiarc-list 1  "oxiarc-list " 
.SH NAME
oxiarc\-list \- List contents of an archive
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBoxiarc\-list\fR [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR] [\fB\-j\fR|\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-T\fR|\fB\-\-tree\fR] [\fB\-s\fR|\fB\-\-sort\fR] [\fB\-r\fR|\fB\-\-reverse\fR] [\fB\-I\fR|\fB\-\-include\fR] [\fB\-X\fR|\fB\-\-exclude\fR] [\fB\-\-lenient\fR] [\fB\-\-memory\-limit\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIARCHIVE\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
List contents of an archive
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Show verbose output
.TP
\fB\-j\fR, \fB\-\-json\fR
Output as JSON (machine\-readable)
.TP
\fB\-T\fR, \fB\-\-tree\fR
Display as directory tree
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-sort\fR \fI<SORT>\fR [default: name]
Sort entries by: name, size, date, or ratio
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
name: Sort by name (alphabetical)
.IP \(bu 2
size: Sort by file size
.IP \(bu 2
date: Sort by modification date
.IP \(bu 2
ratio: Sort by compression ratio (compressed_size / original_size)
.RE
.TP
\fB\-r\fR, \fB\-\-reverse\fR
Reverse sort order
.TP
\fB\-I\fR, \fB\-\-include\fR \fI<INCLUDE>\fR
Include only files matching pattern (glob syntax: *.txt, src/**/*)
.TP
\fB\-X\fR, \fB\-\-exclude\fR \fI<EXCLUDE>\fR
Exclude files matching pattern (glob syntax)
.TP
\fB\-\-lenient\fR
Continue on corruption when reading the archive (emit warnings to stderr)
.TP
\fB\-\-memory\-limit\fR \fI<MEMORY_LIMIT>\fR
Refuse to extract entries exceeding this memory limit (e.g. 100M, 512K, 1G)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
<\fIARCHIVE\fR>
Archive file to list
